From: guillaume <guillaume.chaye@zeetim.com>
Subject: [PATCH] watchdog: gate debug_monitor/hostapd respawn so webui-go owns wifi (nvram gtbe98_wifi_extsup)

Companion to webui-go EnsureRadio (sole-supervisor wifi). The open controller can
bring up the full wifi userspace via wl-ioctls + from-source hostapd (radio config
persists in the driver, never re-applied by wlconf). The one thing that races a
controller-owned hostapd is the stock userspace supervisor: debug_monitor
(dhd_monitor) respawns a killed primary hostapd in ~10s (hostapd only, never wlconf).

On the BE_4916 platform (GT-BE98) the SINGLE rc site that resurrects that supervisor
is the watchdog() tick block guarded by RTCONFIG_HND_ROUTER_BE_4916: when wlready and
debug_monitor is gone it runs start_dhd_monitor() then SIGUSR2 hostapd (re-attach
handshake). The other hostapd-touching watchdog code (wpasupp_hapd_check) is gated by
RPBE58/RTBE58_GO + client_mode and is compiled out on GT-BE98 — irrelevant here.

Gate that block on a new unused nvram flag gtbe98_wifi_extsup (default off, 0024/0028/
0033 early-return model). Flag unset/0 => stock: watchdog keeps debug_monitor alive and
it respawns hostapd (default, safe, behaviour unchanged). Flag=1 => watchdog does NOT
relaunch debug_monitor, so a controller that has taken over (killed debug_monitor) stays
the SOLE hostapd supervisor — webui-go EnsureRadio owns the radios. The flag short-
circuits the existing condition, so with the flag absent the stock code path is taken
verbatim (no behavioural change). It is NOT a function-level return: this block lives
inside the long-running watchdog(int sig) tick, so a return would skip the rest of the
tick — the gate folds into the block's own condition instead.

Re-enable the stock supervisor: nvram unset gtbe98_wifi_extsup ; nvram commit.
See gt-be98-docs (OPEN-RADIO-INIT-RECIPE; wl-ioctl-rc-boundary memory).
---
diff --git a/release/src/router/rc/watchdog.c b/release/src/router/rc/watchdog.c
--- a/release/src/router/rc/watchdog.c
+++ b/release/src/router/rc/watchdog.c
@@ -11643,7 +11643,17 @@
 	}

 #ifdef RTCONFIG_HND_ROUTER_BE_4916
-	if (nvram_get_int("wlready") && !pids("debug_monitor")) {
+	/* Fork GT-BE98 : superviseur wifi externe (webui-go EnsureRadio) possede
+	 * hostapd. debug_monitor (dhd_monitor) est le re-spawn ~10s d'un hostapd
+	 * primaire tue (hostapd seul, jamais wlconf -- la config radio wl-ioctl
+	 * persiste). Ce bloc est le SEUL endroit ou le watchdog ressuscite
+	 * debug_monitor (et resynchronise hostapd via SIGUSR2) sur la plateforme
+	 * BE_4916. Quand gtbe98_wifi_extsup=1, ne pas relancer debug_monitor : le
+	 * controleur webui-go reste l'unique superviseur hostapd (sole-supervisor).
+	 * Defaut off (flag absent/0) => comportement stock inchange.
+	 * Rendre le superviseur stock : nvram unset gtbe98_wifi_extsup ; nvram commit. */
+	if (!nvram_get_int("gtbe98_wifi_extsup") &&
+	    nvram_get_int("wlready") && !pids("debug_monitor")) {
 		dm_count = (dm_count + 1) % 2;
 		if (!dm_count) {
 			start_dhd_monitor();
